revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Categories go at the bottom of this page. -->

This template can make an [[Wikipedia:External links|external link]] to:

* A library holding: An item (book, CD, video, journal, etc.) catalogued in the inventories of various libraries.
* A bibliography: A list of works by or about a subject (i.e., works associated with a particular [[subject heading]]).

Library holdings are tracked by [[WorldCat]], a [[union catalog]] that itemizes the collections of 72,000 libraries in 170 countries and territories.

Bibliographies were available at ''WorldCat Identities'', a project ceased to exist. WorldCat's new [[authority file]] is called ''[[WorldCat Entities]]''.

Sample output: {{WorldCat|id=lccn-n79100628 |name=Murasaki Shikibu}}

==Usage==

===For works===
{{tlx|WorldCat|oclc{{=}}|name{{=}}}}

* {{para|oclc}} is the [[OCLC Control Number]] (OCN) which is an [[accession number (library science)|accession number]], which has 1 to 9 digits.
* {{para|name}} is optional: it overrides the default link label, which is the [[Wikipedia:Page name|page name]]

===For people and subjects===
{{tlx|WorldCat|id{{=}}|name{{=}}}}

* {{para|id}} is a [[Library of Congress Control Number]] with the format {{var|lccn-n00-00000}}.
* {{para|name}} is optional: it overrides the default link label, which is the [[Wikipedia:Page name|page name]].

==Instructions==
===To link to a library item===
# Search [https://search.worldcat.org/ WorldCat] for any other work or service that a library might stock or subscribe to. You can search by title, author, keyword, subject, ISBN, or ISSN. (See the [https://search.worldcat.org/advancedsearch Advanced Search] page for all options.)
# Go to the page of the work, edition, and format that you want.
# Copy the number after ''title/'' in the [[address bar]] of your web browser: {{nowrap|<code><nowiki>https://</nowiki>search.worldcat.org/title/{{highlight|17522144}}</code>}}
# Add the template to the "External links" section of the article.
# Add the OCLC Control Number and (optionally) a name to the template. (The default name is the [[Wikipedia:Page name|page name]].)

You can refine your WorldCat search using the filters. WorldCat includes (but is not limited to): articles, audiobooks, books, e-books, computer files, journals, magazines, maps, movies (BD, DVD, VHS, et al.), music recordings (CD, LP, cassette, et al.), musical scores, newspapers, rare works, theses, TV shows, video games, videos, web services.

Example:
{{tlx|WorldCat|oclc{{=}}17522144|name{{=}}''The Tale of Genji'' (Edward Seidensticker translation)}}

Result:
* {{WorldCat|oclc=17522144 |name=''The Tale of Genji'' (Edward Seidensticker translation)}}

===To link to a bibliography for a person or other subject===
# Search [https://www.worldcat.org/identities/ WorldCat Identities] for the subject.
# Click the name or subject from the list of search results.
# Copy the {{var|lccn}} string from the [[address bar]] of your web browser: {{nowrap|<code><nowiki>https://</nowiki>worldcat.org/identities/{{highlight|lccn-n79100628}}/</code>}}
# Add the template to the "External links" section of the article.
# Add the {{var|lccn}} string and, optionally, a name to the template. (The default name is the [[Wikipedia:Page name|page name]].)


Example:
{{tlx|WorldCat|id{{=}}lccn-n79100628|name{{=}}Murasaki Shikibu}}

Result:
* {{WorldCat|id=lccn-n79100628 |name=Murasaki Shikibu}}

==Maintenance categories==
* {{clc|Pages using WorldCat with unknown parameters}}

== See also ==
{{Wikidata property|P243|P5331|P7859|P10832}}
*[[Faceted Application of Subject Terminology]] (FAST)
*{{tl|VIAF}}
*{{tl|OCLC}}
*{{tl|OCLC search link}}
*{{tl|ISSN}}
*{{tl|ISSN link}}


